To change the color of a <span> on mouse over, you can use CSS. Add the `:hover` pseudo-class to the `span` element and define the desired color:

```html
<span class="hover-color">Text</span>

.hover-color:hover {
  color: #your-color;
}
```

Replace `#your-color` with the desired color value. This will change the color of the `<span>` when the mouse hovers over it.

To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, use the `\footnotemark` command followed by the `\footnotetext` command. Place the `\footnotemark` before the author’s name and the `\footnotetext` after the list. For example:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{footnote}

\begin{document}

\author{Author 1\footnotemark[1], Author 2\footnotemark[1]}
\footnotetext[1]{Footnote text.}

\maketitle

\end{document}
```

This will create a footnote for the authors list with the specified text.

Here's a Python function to sort a list of integers:

```python
def sort_list(numbers):
    return sorted(numbers)
```

This function uses Python's built-in `sorted` function to sort the list of integers in ascending order. You can call it like this: `sort_list([3, 1, 4, 1, 5])`.
